KES Arts, by Kathy Skripek
Our family moved to the Northwest 25 years ago. We came for work and stayed for the serenity
and beauty only found in the Northwest. After working in the high tech field all my career, I
returned to my real passion as an artist in 2002.As a fused glass artist I had a successful
business selling my art to boutiques in Washington for over the last 7 years. My art has been
sold in over a hundred small stores and boutiques such as Made in Washington, Seattle
Nursery and Pacific Northwest Art. I am now focusing on gallery art, working in fused glass,
metal and beeswax or what ever else inspires me. My art work is inspired by nature and
summer days and the beauty of nature that is all around us.
Together KES Art and Black Nugget Farms present to you “The Bee Line”.
